# migrated from tests/cases/same.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test same]
# gen33: equivalence / sameness — pulled by BoolQ #1 ("is house tax and
# property tax are same"). A symmetric relation same(a, b) parrot0 lacked,
# distinct from class membership. We test stated equivalences; deciding
# sameness from prose is out of scope (but reachable via read:). Held-out names.
> housetax is the same as propertytax
< Learned: same(housetax, propertytax).
# Symmetric: order of the two names does not matter.
> are housetax and propertytax the same?
< Yes.
> are propertytax and housetax the same?
< Yes.
# An unrelated pair is not the same -- no guessing.
> are housetax and incometax the same?
< No.
# Identical names are trivially the same.
> are gold and gold the same?
< Yes.
# Equivalence is extractable through the gen32 reader, and still symmetric.
> read: alpha is the same as beta. gamma is a star.
< Learned 2 fact(s), skipped 0.
> are beta and alpha the same?
< Yes.
# Non-transitive by design (Decision D-2026-06-15f): a=b and b=c is not a=c.
> beta is the same as delta
< Learned: same(beta, delta).
> are alpha and delta the same?
< No.
